# Firebase Configuration
#
# REQUIRED for both local development and production deployment
# Get these values from your Firebase project settings in the Google Cloud Console
# https://console.firebase.google.com/
#
# HOW TO GET THESE VALUES:
# 1. Go to https://console.firebase.google.com/
# 2. Select your project
# 3. Click the gear icon (⚙️) → Project Settings
# 4. Scroll down to "Your apps" section
# 5. Find your web app (marked with </> icon)
# 6. Copy each value from the config object below:

VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=

# Optional: Firebase Analytics ID (only needed if Analytics is enabled)
VITE_FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID=

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# FOR LOCAL DEVELOPMENT:
# 1. Create .env file in the root directory:
#    cp .env.example .env
# 2. Fill in the Firebase values above
# 3. Run: npm run dev
# 4. Dev server starts at http://localhost:5173

# FOR NETLIFY DEPLOYMENT:
# 1. Push this repo to GitHub
# 2. Go to https://app.netlify.com
# 3. Click "Add new site" → "Import an existing project"
# 4. Select your GitHub repository
# 5. Netlify will auto-detect the build settings (npm run build → dist/)
# 6. After deploy creation, go to Site Settings → Environment
# 7. Click "Add environment variables" and add EACH variable below:
#    - VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY
#    - VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN
#    - VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID
#    - VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET
#    - VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID
#    - VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID
#    - VITE_FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID (optional)
# 8. Trigger a new deploy from Netlify dashboard
# 9. Your app will be live at: https://your-site-name.netlify.app

# FOR GITHUB BRANCH DEPLOYS (Preview URLs):
# Every push to any branch creates an automatic preview:
# - Feature branch: https://feature-name--your-site-name.netlify.app
# - Pull requests: Auto-preview comments on the PR
# These use the same Firebase credentials as production

